-- Bank of England Said to Hire Banks for Dollar Bond Sale
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-02-21T15:11:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/bank-of-england-said-to-hire-banks-for-dollar-bond-sale.html
The  Bank of England  plans to sell
three-year bonds in dollars, according to a banker involved in
the transaction.  Bank of America Corp., Goldman Sachs Group Inc.,  HSBC
Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and Morgan Stanley are managing the deal, the
banker said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  